[[Alam al Mulk]] (''the kingdom'') is a term of [[islamic cosmology]] and refers to the realm, representing the physical plane, including medicine, engineering and everything, that can be perceived by the five senses.<ref>Vincent J. Cornell ''Voices of Islam: Voices of the spirit'' Greenwood Publishing Group 2007 {{ISBN|978-0-275-98734-3}} page 129</ref> Higher Realms are not thought to be spatial, rather a ''higher realm'' means, it impinges the realms below. The physical plane is therefore influenced by [[Malakut|Alam al Malakut]] (imaginal realm) and which is in turn impinged by [[Alam al Jabarut]] (the spiritual world).<ref>Victor Danner ''Kitāb Al-Ḥikam'' Brill Archive 1984 {{ISBN|978-9-004-07168-1}} page 71</ref>
