==== Hélas ==== ''Hélas'' is not aspirated in classical poetry. * ''Hélas ! Que cet hélas a de peine à sortir'' ([[Pierre Corneille]]). That is indicated here by the use of ''cet'' rather than ''ce''.
=== Words beginning with ''hi'' === The aspiration of ''h'' is often optional in words beginning with ''hi'', and the liaison (with a mute ''h'') is generally accepted, except in recent anglicisms of current usage, interjections or homophones with another word. Beside the very productive and learned Greek root ''hiéro-'', most words are quite recent and of Germanic origin ([[German language|German]], [[Dutch language|Dutch]], Modern English), or the ''h'' is lightly pronounced.
