=== Words beginning with ''ho''=== Most have an aspirated ''h''. The exceptions are mostly Latin roots that are most widely used in which the ''h'' has lost its voicing through assimilation to common language (in ''hôte'', ''hospice'' or ''hôpital'' all derived from ''hospes''/''hospitis''. Also if the ''h'' has been assimilated to the following ⟨s⟩ ''heure''/''horo-'', taken from ''hora'' in which the ''h'' has been assimilated to the preceding adjectives, make the ''h'' mute.
