{{about|a political party founded in 1973||Socialist Workers' Party of Finland}} {{Infobox political party |name = Socialist Workers' Party |native_name = Sosialistinen Työväenpuolue |lang1 = |name_lang1 = |logo = |colorcode = red |leader = |chairperson = |president = |secretary_general = |spokesperson = |founder = |slogan = |founded = {{Start date|1973|05|5}}<ref name=MMM75>Mitä missä milloin 1975 (Otava 1974), p. 178.</ref> |dissolved = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> |split = [[Social Democratic Union of Workers and Smallholders|Socialist Union of Workers and Smallholders]] |merged = [[Left Alliance (Finland)|Left Alliance]] |successor = |headquarters = |newspaper = ''[[Päivän Uutiset]]'' 1973–1976 |student_wing = |youth_wing = [[Socialist Youth League of Finland]] |wing1_title = Women's wing |wing1 = [[Social Democratic Women's League of Finland]] |wing2_title = Children's wing |wing2 = [[Varhaisnuorisoliitto Haukat]] |wing3_title = |wing3 = |membership_year = |membership = |ideology = [[Socialism]] |position = [[Left-wing politics|Left-wing]] |religion = |national = |international = |european = |europarl = |affiliation1_title = |affiliation1 = |colors = <!-- use "colours" for British English --> |symbol = |flag = |website = |country = Finland |footnotes = }}
'''Socialist Workers' Party''' ({{lang-fi|Sosialistinen Työväenpuolue}}, {{lang-sv|Socialistiska Arbetarepartiet}}) was a political party in [[Finland]]. The STP was founded in 1973 as split from [[Social Democratic Union of Workers and Smallholders]] (TPSL). STP emerged from a group that did not approve of the return of TPSL to the [[Social Democratic Party of Finland|Social Democratic Party]].
STP had electoral alliances with [[Finnish People's Democratic League]] (SKDL), the mass front dominated by the [[Communist Party of Finland]] (SKP) but with little success. When SKP (and SKDL) split in 1985-1986 STP cooperated with [[Democratic Alternative (Finland)|Democratic Alternative]] which was founded by [[Communist Party of Finland (1997)|Communist Party of Finland (Unity)]] (SKPy).
In February 1990, STP chairman [[Pentti Waltzer]] said the party would join the new [[Left Alliance (Finland)|Left Alliance]] if Democratic Alternative decided to merge with it,<ref>Marja Haapio & Matti Virtanen: [http://www.hs.fi/arkisto/artikkeli/900208085 Vasemmistoliiton "torikokous" kerää monenlaisia sosialisteja] (Helsingin Sanomat 8.2.1990)</ref> which later happened.
